    slug: "islamic-studies-grade-vol-10",
    description: `Islamic Studies Grade Volume 10 is an advanced-level textbook designed for students who have progressed through the earlier volumes of this comprehensive Islamic studies series. Published by Darussalam, this volume targets students at the higher secondary level and assumes a solid foundation in the basic principles of Islam that were established in the preceding nine volumes. The content at this level is significantly more detailed and analytical, challenging students to engage with complex theological, legal, and historical concepts in a manner that prepares them for higher Islamic education or for navigating the intellectual challenges they will face as adult Muslims in the modern world. The book covers advanced topics in aqeedah (Islamic creed), including detailed discussions on the attributes of Allah, the concept of qadar (divine predestination) and its relationship with human free will, the status of the companions of the Prophet, and the correct Islamic approach to differences of opinion among scholars. The fiqh (jurisprudence) section at this level goes beyond basic rulings to explore the principles behind Islamic law (usul al-fiqh), helping students understand how scholars derive rulings from the primary sources and why legitimate differences of opinion exist. Topics in Islamic history covered in this volume include the later period of the Abbasid Caliphate, the Crusades, the Mongol invasions, and the contributions of Muslim civilisation to fields such as science, medicine, mathematics, and philosophy during its golden age. The book also addresses contemporary issues that Muslim youth frequently encounter, providing Islamic perspectives on topics such as ethics in science and technology, the relationship between Muslims and non-Muslims in pluralistic societies, and the challenges of maintaining Islamic identity in the modern world. The language and tone of the book are appropriately mature for the target age group, while remaining clear and accessible. Each chapter includes thought-provoking discussion questions, research assignments, and analytical exercises that develop critical thinking skills alongside religious knowledge. This volume serves as an important bridge between the foundational Islamic education of the earlier grades and the more specialised study that students may pursue at the university level or in Islamic seminaries, making it a crucial component of any comprehensive Islamic studies programme.`,
    metaDescription: "Islamic Studies Grade Vol 10 is an advanced textbook on Islamic creed, fiqh principles, civilisational contributions, and contemporary issues."
